# The Soup of Lies

**Intro**
Tonight, only the truth will be exposed in a few verses. 
But especially my favorite recipe : the soupe of lies.

**Verses**
I've been telling lies for years now.
What's the point of telling them,
the damage is done,
I'm no more nervous now

I don't know where to start
so many things to say ...
but if it'll set me free
I'll accept their wrath

It's exhausting in the long run
I feel like I'm at the end of my rope
the curtain has to fall
it's time for me to strive

Tired of being left behind
I ended up making up a life for myself
Tonight I'll take the shame
Tonight I'll will face denial

**Chorus**
Ce soir c'est décidé j'arrête
de vous rouler comme un pâtissier
de vous jouer le même refrain comme un musicien
de vous mythonner comme un cuisinier
J'attendrai plus demain pour être serein,
pour devenir le mec qui fait les choses bien
Finit les doutes, finit la soupe

**Verses**
I can tell by your reaction
that you aren't thrilled
If I had been paying attention
what would have changed

My dreams turned to lies
the fiction became the truth
a life of encounter
of people all imagined

Alone　in my house in turmoil
allegory of my passion
But none of that down here,
just me and my illusions

Falsehoods instead of dates
Tales instead of restaurants
Tonight I had enough
Tonigh I confess everything

**Chorus**
Ce soir c'est décidé j'arrête
de vous mener en bateau comme un matelot
de vous enfûmer comme un fermier
de vous faire des promesses sans lendemain comme un politicien
J'attendrai plus demain pour être serein,
pour devenir le mec qui fait les choses bien
Finit les doutes, finit la soupe

**Outro**
I'm not the interesting guy
not the one that makes people laugh
just the guy who tells fables.
so much so that he loses count

